The paper proposes a novel architecture for visual navigation in complex environments using deep reinforcement learning. The paper focuses on the use of memory and attention mechanisms to address the long-term memory issue in navigation. The paper also presents detailed convergence analysis of the proposed architecture. Based on these factors, the most likely sub-category is cs.RO (Robotics and Control). However, the paper also heavily relies on computer vision techniques for visual navigation, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.CV (Computer Vision) or cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The use of deep learning and reinforcement learning also suggests that it could belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) or cs.SY (Systems and Control).
